<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Porter" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Porter,</orth> 1) one that carries burdens: <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.200" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 270</bibl>. cf. the name <emph>Tale-porter</emph> (i. e. talebearer) in <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.273" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 273</bibl>.<lb />2) a doorkeeper: <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 213</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 36</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 3, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 4, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 4, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 5, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 64</bibl>.
